FeedPackage.ReleaseNotes: - Fixes - Fix an issue with the `CheckAlertsUpdate` method from interface *Linxo.Client.Interfaces.Services*.**IAlertService** when alerts update were not correctly identified - Fix an issue with the `AcceptTermsAndConditions` method from interface *Linxo.Client.Interfaces.Services*.**IAuthenticationService** where property `AskForTermsAndConditions` was not updated to correct value - Changes - Change signatures of two methods in interface *Linxo.Client.Interfaces.Services*.**IAuthenticationService** - `void AcceptTermsAndConditions()` is now : `Task AcceptTermsAndConditions()` - `void ClearToken()` is now : `Task ClearToken()` - Change base class for **AuthorizeDeviceResult** and **LoginDeviceResult** in *Linxo.Client.Actions.Auth* to use abstract class *Linxo.Client.Actions.Auth*.**AuthenticateDeviceResultBase** - Change behavior of methods `AuthorizeDevice` and `LoginDevice` to not load the session if property `AskForTermsAndConditions` set to true after authentication - Change behavior of method `AcceptTermsAndConditions` in interface *Linxo.Client.Interfaces.Services*.**IAuthenticationService** to load the session if not already loaded - Replace interface *Linxo.Client.Interfaces.Services*.**IAppDeviceConfig** by new class *Linxo.Client.Config*.**AppDeviceConfig** : - Change in interface *Linxo.Client.Interfaces.Services*.**IServiceHub** : - Property `AppDeviceConfig` returns now an instance of the class *Linxo.Client.Config*.**AppDeviceConfig** - Change in class *Linxo.Client.Services*.**ServiceHub** : - Constructor `ServiceHub(IAppDeviceConfig appDeviceConfig, IAppStorage appStorage, IEventPublisher eventPublisher, ILoggingService loggingService = null)` is now `ServiceHub(AppDeviceConfig appDeviceConfig, IAppStorage appStorage, IEventPublisher eventPublisher, ILoggingService loggingService = null)` - Change in interface *Linxo.Client.Interfaces.Services*.**IAuthenticationService** : - Property `AppDeviceConfig` returns now an instance of the class *Linxo.Client.Config*.**AppDeviceConfig** - **AlertsUpdateEvent** : raised when the alerts have been changed (contains the added and removed alerts)

FeedPackage.Description: Ad-hoc visual query builder for your applications
FeedPackage.Summary: Use EasyQuery to provide a friendly user interface for advanced search and filtration of the data in your applications. Our components allow your users (or web-site visitors) get the information they need on their own, quickly and easily without any assistance from you or your support team.
FeedPackage.Title: EasyQuery.Mvc.Scaffolding

FeedPackage.Description:
EasyQuery components implement a convenient visual query builder in your application and will be a useful addition to any application or website that requires some advanced searching and/or filtering functionality.
Unlike other query builders that require users to have some knowledge about relational database concepts, tables, joins, etc., our query builder components allow you to construct a query visually: simply by assembling a phrase in natural language.
EasyQuery supports different query languages (SQL, Entity SQL, Linq, Filter expression) and all popular databases: SQL Server, MySQL, Oracle, Access, Postgre SQL, etc.

This package is part of the Accord.NET Framework.
FeedPackage.Summary: Matrix library, matrix decompositions (QR, SVD, LU, Cholesky, NMF), linear and non-linear optimization, constrained problem solvers, readers for MATLAB/Octave .MAT files, random number generation and others.
FeedPackage.Tags: accord.net aforge.net framework math decompositions lu qr constrained optimization differentiation numerical matrix algebra svd kernel quadratic programming linear regression
